title: Computer Science I
description: Introduction to algorithm design and problem‑solving techniques using a high‑level programming language.
prereqs: MAC 2311C (Calculus I) with a C (2.0) or better.
notes: Computer Science, Computer Engineering, IT majors.

title: Computer Science II
description: Advanced data structures and algorithms including linked lists, trees, graphs, sorting, and searching.
prereqs: COP 3502 with a C (2.0) or better.
notes: Computer Science, Computer Engineering, IT majors.

title: General Physics I
description: Fundamental principles of mechanics, oscillations, and wave motion. Includes problem‑solving and conceptual understanding.
prereqs: MAC 2311C (Calculus I) with a C (2.0) or better, or C.I.
coreqs: PHY 2048L (1 credit) is a required co‑requisite.

title: General Physics II
description: Fundamental principles of electricity, magnetism, and optics. Includes problem‑solving and conceptual understanding.
prereqs: PHY 2048 with a C (2.0) or better or C.I.
coreqs: PHY 2049L (1 credit) is a required co‑requisite.

title: Calculus I
description: Limits, derivatives, and integrals of functions of a single variable, and applications.
prereqs: MAC 1140 (Precalculus Algebra) and MAC 1114 (Trigonometry) with a C (2.0) or better, or Math Placement Test score.

title: Composition I
description: Focuses on developing effective written communication skills, including argumentation, analysis, and research. Required for all undergraduate degrees.
prereqs: Placement into ENC 1101 through SAT, ACT, PERT scores, or ENC 1100.
notes: Usually taken in the first year.

title: Chemistry Fundamentals I
description: Basic principles of chemistry including atomic structure, bonding, stoichiometry, and states of matter. Designed for science and engineering majors.
prereqs: CHM 1025 or placement test, or high school chemistry with a good grade.
coreqs: CHM 2045L (1 credit) is a required co‑requisite.
